1 olive oil
1 portion cauliflower
1 carrot
¾ cup water
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 packet couscous
1 bag baby spinach leaves
½ box Crushed & Sieved Tomatoes
1 tsp honey
1 box coconut milk
10 g butter
1 packet flaked almonds
3 clove garlic
1 sachet Middle Eastern spice blend
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut the cauliflower into small florets. Cut the carrot into bite-sized chunks. Place the cauliflower and carrot on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

While the veggies are roasting, add the water and vegetable stock powder to a medium saucepan and bring to the boil. Add the couscous and a drizzle of olive oil. Stir to combine, cover with a lid and remove from the heat. Set aside until all the water is absorbed, 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork.

While the couscous is cooking, finely chop the garlic. Roughly chop the baby spinach leaves. Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat. Toast the flaked almonds, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

Return the frying pan to a medium-heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the garlic and Middle Eastern seasoning until fragrant, 30 seconds. Add the crushed & sieved tomatoes, the honey and coconut milk and cook until the sauce has thickened, 2-3 minutes.

Remove the pan from heat, then add the roasted veggies, baby spinach and the butter. Stir until the spinach has just wilted, 1-2 minutes.

Divide the couscous between bowls. Top with the creamy cauliflower tagine and Greek-style yoghurt. Sprinkle over the toasted almonds to serve.